        <tr valign="top"> 
          <td style="border-bottom: 1px double" colspan="3"> 
            <p><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Instead of wasting 
              valuable and hard-to-find runes getting your Research skill up to 
              par, you can<b> </b>now use practice recipes to improve your research 
              skill. </font></p>
            <p><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">To find out 
              what combinations of items will advance your Research skill, do 
              one of the following:</font></p>
            <ul>
              <li><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">If you are 
                a <b>good wizard</b>, go to Mrysil the Gypsy in the Gypsy camp 
                of North Karana. Hail her and then give either a Lightstone or 
                a Greater Lightstone. Giving her a Lightstone will give you one 
                of the two combination guides for Practice Research, Runes and 
                Research Book 1 or Book 2. Giving her a Greater Lightstone will 
                cause her to give you the Concordance of Research, which is the 
                place you use to combine the Practice Research components in.</font></li>
              <li><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">If you are 
                an <b>evil wizard</b>, go to Smith Tv'ysa as the merchant camp 
                in South Ro. Give her a Lightstone for the Runes and Research 
                books 1 and 2, and a Greater Lightstone for the Concordance of 
                Research.</font></li>
            </ul>
          </td>
